ResourceHeader.ResourceName: International Monitor for Auroral Geomagnetic Effects (IMAGE) Finnish Meterological Institute 10 s Ground Magnetometer Data
ResourceHeader.AlternateName: IMAGE FMI 10 s Ground Magnetometer Data
ResourceHeader.Description:
The International Monitor for Auroral Geomagnetic Effects (IMAGE) consists of 52 magnetometer stations maintained by 10 institutes from Finland, Germany, Norway, Poland, Russia, Sweden, Denmark, and Iceland. The prime objectives of IMAGE are to study auroral electrojets and moving two-dimensional current systems. The long profile covering geographic latitudes from 51 to 82 degrees is especially favorable for electrojet studies. Together with other ground-based recordings (by radars, riometers, all-sky cameras) and satellite observations, IMAGE is an essential part in the investigations of high-latitude magnetospheric-ionospheric physics. Together with its predecessor, the EISCAT magnetometer cross started in 1982, IMAGE also provides high-quality data useful for studies of geomagnetic induction and long-term geomagnetic activity in the auroral region.
		 
		 The Finnish Meterological Institute operates the following stations:  ALT, KAU, KEV, MAS, KIL, IVA, MUO, PEL, RAN, OUJ, MEK, HAN, NUR, and TAR.

PublicationInfo.Authors: Juusola, L., Viljanen, A., Ryno, J. A., Gustafsson, J., and Kellinsalmi, M.

Parameter.Name: Length of one record
Parameter.Description: Length of one record. 3 characters [in minutes].

Parameter.Name: Type of data
Parameter.Description: Type of data 2 characters [00 = observatory; 01 = temporary station]

Parameter.Name: Geographic latitude
Parameter.Description: Geographic latitude 5 characters [in 0.01o (space or sign and 4 numbers)].

Parameter.Name: Minute
Parameter.Description: Minute 2 characters [00...59. The first minute of the record]

Parameter.Name: How data produced.
Parameter.Description: How data produced 1 character [0 = digital recording; 1 = digitized from primary recordings; 2 = digitized from supplementary recording; 9 = unknown].

Parameter.Name: Filter breakpoint
Parameter.Description: Filter breakpoint 4 characters [0000 if values are means between datapoints. Otherwize period in seconds at which low pass filter is 3 db down (0.7 amplitude). 9999 if no filtering was employed.]

Parameter.Name: Filter slope
Parameter.Description: Filter slope 2 characters [Number of db per octave, i.e. 6, 12, 18 db/octave or measured equivalent for numerical filter.]

Parameter.Name: Base line information.
Parameter.Description: Base line information 1 character [1 = final data, absolute base line, accuracy about 1 nT; 2 = final data but no absolute measurements; 3 = preliminary data; 4 = data relative to quiet day night values.], Probable base line change 2 characters [in 0.1 nT within one day].

Parameter.Name: Probable base line change
Parameter.Description: Probable base line change 2 characters [in 0.1 nT within one day]

Parameter.Name: Components
Parameter.Description: Components 1 character [1 = X ,Y, Z; 2 = H, D (0.1), Z; 3 = A, B, Z]. For the 10 s resolution this should always be 1.

Parameter.Name: Character of the day
Parameter.Description: Character of the day 1 character [0 = normal; 1 = one of the 5 international quietest days; 2 = one of the 5 international disturbed days]
